AGI -&nbsp;It is a miracle made architecture. It is the spiritual rebirth of the man who begins with the assumption of the consecrated host. The prodigy is symbolized by the monumental Vatican Baldacchino». Built between 1624 and 1633 by a Gian Lorenzo Bernini >neanche trentenne, the Baroque masterpiece is located above the tomb of the apostle Peter.
The doctrine of the Church explains that the renewal of the Christian is an inner transformation: begins with Mass and culminates with the Eucharist. The art complex shows this path. First metaphor is the new life expressed by the leaves of vine (also of laurus and laurel) which are entangled on the four tortile columns). The second transformation, on the other hand, lies in the passage of the being, from the material to the spiritual dimension, symbolized by the altar at the bottom and the sphere at the top of the Baldacchino.
Other artistic elements appear on the structure. On the marbles and on the bronze columns, in fact, “fly” the bees of the Barberini, the noble lineage of which belongs the pontiff who has so much beauty. But it wasn't always like that. Once the symbol of the house was the tafano, from which the Tafani da Barberino. Evidently, however, the appearance of the insect must have appeared little pleasant if later the family chose to be represented by the colorful and laborious bee. And then there is also another subject of the animal kingdom that seems to hide between the vegetation on the stems. It is the lizard.> They count more than one. The first reptile is to mean the Resurrection >: the animal regularly changes skin and its tail, if cut, is able to regrow, to reborn.
