The lawyers of the consort have pointed out that since the winning was obtained when the spouses were still married and in the regime of communion of the goods, the sum automatically falls into the common heritage and must be divided to 50%. For the Cassation, in fact, the winnings of the national lottery and games fall into the legal communion of the spouses even if the play was made with the personal money of only one of the two.
